Rating: 3
I made this recipe for my husband who absolutely LOVES curry--and he absolutely LOVED this recipe! The only changes I made were that I only added about 1/4 of the ginger called for, added mushrooms as one of the other reviewers had mentioned, added about 1/4 to 1/3 teaspoon of cayenne pepper to zip it up a little, and thickened it just a bit with a solution of 1 tablespoon of cornstarch and 2 tablespoons of water. It went over really well with my family--it was VERY good!

Rating: 3
This recipe shows promise. It came out way too salty on my first try so I added 3/4 cup of heavy cream to try to salvage it. The cream sure didn't hurt it and probably improved how the recipe is supposed to taste by adding a lovely richness to the sauce. I browned the chicken first before adding the other ingredients. I omitted the potatoes and substituted 2 cups of sliced mushrooms. Then I let the curry age for two days in the fridge and voila - it was pretty tasty! Next time, I'll probably add peas to the dish and omit the soy sauce or try a different curry powder (the Madras curry I used contained salt and that could have been the problem).

